{"TopicId":222180,"ForumId":208,"TopicTitle":"\u0027Clear Workspace\u0027 opens a prompt that makes it seem like the game will delete the workspace save when used","CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-27T16:43:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-27T16:43:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003ECustomFlags | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Win 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i7-3770K | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0GTK 1060 6GB | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32 GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nGo to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E in an existing save\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nDiscover there\u0027s already a craft there that you were working on before\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nClick the new craft icon because you want to start a new one\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002209uz4LT.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002280.95\u0022 height=\u002251\u0022 width=\u002263\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/09uz4LT.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nThis prompt appears:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00229P6vGtq.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002229.98\u0022 height=\u0022304\u0022 width=\u00221014\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/9P6vGtq.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe word \u0022delete\u0022 here is scary. It makes it sound like the game is going to remove files from disk.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut more importantly, the only two options are to \u0022delete\u0022 the current build or not create a new craft at all. Neither of these is adequate to the main thing players will expect from this button, which is to clear the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0\u003Ci\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Ewithout\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/i\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003Elosing data\u003Ci\u003E\u003C/i\u003E. There should be a third button along the lines of \u0022Save and Clear\u0022, which saves any changes to the current craft before emptying out the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E for a new craft. This should probably be the default option when this prompt appears, because \u0022deleting\u0022 isn\u0027t what anyone wants, and cancelling is only for mis-clicks, a corner case.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr for an even better UX, have it auto-save the current craft and clear the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E without any prompt at all! One easy click!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-27T17:02:44Z\u0022 title=\u002212/27/2023 05:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 27\u0022\u003EDecember 27, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by The Space Peacock\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Space Peacock","CreatedById":224498,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-27T17:03:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/156657-hebarusan/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022156657\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/156657-hebarusan/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@HebaruSan\u003C/a\u003E edited the title of your report to make it more clear what the issue is\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-27T17:15:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224352701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022222180\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703696598\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022224498\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Space Peacock\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, The Space Peacock said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/156657-hebarusan/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022156657\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/156657-hebarusan/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@HebaruSan\u003C/a\u003E edited the title of your report to make it more clear what the issue is\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe issue is the poor usability of this popup, insofar as it presents two bad options. That can\u0027t be fixed just by rephrasing them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}